# Robust Rules for Windsurf Cascade (Astro Titan Core Theme)

1. Imports & File Structure
    • Use absolute aliases for imports: @components, @data, @assets.
    • Organize pages in src/pages/[lang]/… (e.g., src/pages/en/index.astro). Start with en; add es within a week.
    • Store repeatable content (e.g., features, stats) in src/content using Astro Content Collections.

2. Type Safety
    • Enable strict and strictNullChecks in tsconfig.json. Disable noUncheckedIndexedAccess to reduce complexity.
    • Declare export interface Props in each .astro file for component props.
    • Run pnpm astro check locally during development; CI treats type errors as warnings, not blockers.

3. UI & Styling
    • Wrap every page in @layouts/Layout.astro, passing title, description, and lang props.
    • Limit button variant prop to "primary" | "secondary" | "whatsapp".
    • Use CSS variables for styling (defined in src/styles/tokens.css). Inline styles are allowed for prototyping but must be refactored before merging.
    • Maintain a minimal token set (e.g., colors, spacing) in src/styles/tokens.css. Example:
:root {
  --color-primary: #007bff;
  --color-secondary: #6c757d;
  --spacing-sm: 8px;
  --spacing-md: 16px;
}

4. Internationalization (i18n)
    • Support en and es locales. New features launch in en first, with es added within a week.
    • Translate alt text and meta descriptions. Use t('key') helpers for dynamic paths (e.g., t('services.public-speaking.slug')).
    • CI checks homepage and key routes (/en, /es, /en/services/*) for 404s or missing translations.

5. Performance
    • Use Astro’s <Image> component for images, with AVIF/WEBP formats and LQIP placeholders.
    • Target JS bundle size ≤ 300 kB and CLS-impacting CSS ≤ 150 kB.
    • Run Lighthouse on /en and /es homepages, targeting LCP < 3s and CLS < 0.15.

6. QA & CI
    • CI pipeline runs pnpm lint, pnpm build, and basic Playwright E2E tests (e.g., homepage, navigation).
    • ESLint rules: no-console and no-debugger are warnings, not errors.
    • Pre-commit hooks (via Husky/lint-staged) run prettier --write only.

7. Development Workflow
    • Use pnpm astro dev for local preview.
    • Restart VS Code TypeScript server if IntelliSense stalls.
    • Run pnpm astro check --watch in a side terminal for type checking during development.

8. Release & Deployment
    • Use Conventional Commits for clear versioning (e.g., feat: add button variant).
    • Verify builds with pnpm astro build before deployment.
    • Deploy via Platform.sh; staging branch auto-deploys a preview environment.

9. Governance & Code-Review Checklist
    • Locale parity (homepage and key routes) achieved
    • Inline styles refactored or justified
    • Lighthouse LCP < 3s, CLS < 0.15 for homepages
    • Basic E2E tests (homepage, navigation) added
    • Bundle size ≤ 300 kB JS, ≤ 150 kB CSS
    Key strings (alt text, meta descriptions) localized